comment.body:
@CMik responding to yesterday, she wouldn’t hold those puts because, as I mentioned in the post, she has said they are overpriced and would be subject to decay, even as price falls, into March OPEX. Isn’t that what happens in an environment where vol increases on spikes and decreases on declines?

Also, I mentioned that spot is now close to where she bought those puts in the first place, so given 5 days have passed, wouldn’t Theta decay still be a thing? On Friday morning she still affirmed in her intraday post that she was indeed holding those puts and didn’t take any profits. I would assume they were highly green after open before the MASSIVE rally. So I doubt they are “already in the money” still. They are likely down a bit from where she bought them. So that’s all I was mentioning. 

Still learning this stuff so I’m probably inaccurate.

